creator: Files.fm
descriptionHtml:
Files.fm is a data storage platform that helps users and companies securely store and conveniently transfer large amounts of data.

This is the new mobile version that includes the ability to automatically back up and free up space on your phone.

Why choose Files.fm and upgrade to Pro:

- Private data storage at a good price
- Unlimited traffic and fast data loading
- Preview and stream video, audio and other files
- Convert docs to PDF, video to MP4

- Online Document editing and collaboration
- Automatic Antivirus scans
- Option to sell content and receive payments
- Secure and General Data Protection Regulation compliant

- Pro max 20GB web file size, custom for Business
- Set passwords on links and expiration dates
- Large volume synchronization and network drive (webdav)
- e-signature support, comments and file tagging

- Disable file downloads - view only mode
- Advanced search and optional character recognition
- File access, download stats and detailed security log
- Content embedding on your website or API integration
descriptionShort: Easiest way to store and share files!

appDetails.recentChangesHtml:
Improvements:
— new grid view
— new document viewer
— file gallery UX and speed improvements
— performance tuning and preloading
— bug fixes related to file download and permissions

We are currently working on “Share to” and the search, which will be available in the next version.

creator: Files.fm
descriptionHtml:
Files.fm - Secure Cloud Storage & File Backup

The Files.fm app is a robust cloud storage solution that empowers you to securely upload, backup, store, share, and manage your files effortlessly across all your devices. Designed for personal and professional use, Files.fm makes it easy to keep your files safe, accessible, and organized—whether you’re handling photos, videos, documents, or entire folders.

Key Features

- Automatic Folder Backup & Sync: Select specific folders to auto-backup to your Files.fm cloud account (one-way sync) or manually upload entire folders from your device. Never worry about losing important files!

- Seamless Large File Uploads: Easily upload large video files in their original quality, preserving every detail.

- Multi-Platform Access: Enjoy access to your Files.fm account across Web, Android, Android TV, iOS, Windows, and macOS with automatic sync across all platforms.

- Photo Galleries & Sharing: Create beautiful photo galleries to share with friends or colleagues, complete with options to set link expiration dates, passwords, and download permissions.

Why Upgrade to Files.fm PRO or Business?

Unlock additional features with a PRO subscription for a more powerful, secure, and seamless experience.

- Private Cloud & Enhanced Security: Get dedicated, private cloud storage with advanced security features, including detailed access logs, password-protected links, and GDPR compliance.

- Faster Upload Speeds: Save time and upload files faster with prioritized uploads.

- Media Streaming & File Conversion: Stream videos and audio directly from your Files.fm cloud, and convert documents to PDF or videos to MP4 for seamless viewing.

- Powerful File Management: Access file versions, undelete accidentally deleted files, and organize with tags, comments, and advanced search options (by name, tags, and descriptions).

- Automatic Antivirus Scans: Keep your files safe with built-in antivirus scanning, ensuring that everything uploaded is secure.

- Extensive Device Sync & API Integrations: Sync large volumes of data across multiple devices and integrate seamlessly using the REST API for custom workflows and app connections.

With Files.fm, experience reliable cloud storage with advanced features tailored to meet the needs of today’s digital world. Download now to simplify your file management, backup important data, and stay connected wherever you go.
descriptionShort: Backup, Upload, Store, Share and Manage your content

appDetails.recentChangesHtml:
- Uploading files will now be faster and take up less storage space because the app no longer needs to cache all uploaded files
- Small fixes
